    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Furniture arms in which the support rises from the seat rail curving first toward the front and then toward the back, and leveling out for the armrest. Used in the Queen Anne and Early Georgian periods.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000040371/Tomlin, English Furniture (1972)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Meubelarmen waarvan de leuning hoger wordt vanaf het zitvlak, die eerst naar de voorkant buigen en dan naar de achterkant, en breder worden voor de armleuning. Wordt gebruikt in de Queen Anne en vroeg Georgiaanse tijd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>家具扶手的一種，扶手柱從座椅邊框先往前延伸，再向後屈伸，最後拉至水平形成扶手。在安妮女王（Queen Anne）時代與喬治王朝早期採用此形式的扶手。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
